#: ../../../reference/urllib3.request.rst:2
msgid "urllib3.request()"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:1
msgid ""
"A convenience, top-level request method. It uses a module-global "
"``PoolManager`` instance. Therefore, its side effects could be shared across "
"dependencies relying on it. To avoid side effects create a new "
"``PoolManager`` instance and use it instead. The method does not accept low-"
"level ``**urlopen_kw`` keyword arguments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../reference/urllib3.request.rst:0
msgid "Parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:6
msgid "HTTP request method (such as GET, POST, PUT, etc.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:9
msgid "The URL to perform the request on."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:12
msgid ""
"Data to send in the request body, either :class:`str`, :class:`bytes`, an "
"iterable of :class:`str`/:class:`bytes`, or a file-like object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:16
msgid "Data to encode and send in the request body."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:19
msgid ""
"Dictionary of custom headers to send, such as User-Agent, If-None-Match, etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:23
msgid "If True, the response's body will be preloaded into memory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:26
msgid ""
"If True, will attempt to decode the body based on the 'content-encoding' "
"header."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:30
msgid ""
"If True, automatically handle redirects (status codes 301, 302, 303, 307, "
"308). Each redirect counts as a retry. Disabling retries will disable "
"redirect, too."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:35
msgid ""
"Configure the number of retries to allow before raising a :class:`~urllib3."
"exceptions.MaxRetryError` exception.  If ``None`` (default) will retry 3 "
"times, see ``Retry.DEFAULT``. Pass a :class:`~urllib3.util.retry.Retry` "
"object for fine-grained control over different types of retries. Pass an "
"integer number to retry connection errors that many times, but no other "
"types of errors. Pass zero to never retry.  If ``False``, then retries are "
"disabled and any exception is raised immediately. Also, instead of raising a "
"MaxRetryError on redirects, the redirect response will be returned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:36
msgid ""
"Configure the number of retries to allow before raising a :class:`~urllib3."
"exceptions.MaxRetryError` exception."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:39
msgid ""
"If ``None`` (default) will retry 3 times, see ``Retry.DEFAULT``. Pass a :"
"class:`~urllib3.util.retry.Retry` object for fine-grained control over "
"different types of retries. Pass an integer number to retry connection "
"errors that many times, but no other types of errors. Pass zero to never "
"retry."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:45
msgid ""
"If ``False``, then retries are disabled and any exception is raised "
"immediately. Also, instead of raising a MaxRetryError on redirects, the "
"redirect response will be returned."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:51
msgid ""
"If specified, overrides the default timeout for this one request. It may be "
"a float (in seconds) or an instance of :class:`urllib3.util.Timeout`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/urllib3/__init__.py:docstring
#: of urllib3.request:56
msgid ""
"Data to encode and send as JSON with UTF-encoded in the request body. The "
"``\"Content-Type\"`` header will be set to ``\"application/json\"`` unless "
"specified otherwise."
msgstr ""

